A certificate that I find to be very meaningful – a first aid certificate.
This is one of the skill certificates that I consider to be important, besides my driver’s license!
Let’s make it clear: First aid measures are actually emergency responses taken in the event of sudden incidents, that is, the rescue efforts carried out before the ambulance arrives.
As is well known, there is actually a certain amount of time that passes before the ambulance arrives after an accident occurs, and it is precisely this period that is the most critical.
This is the moment when emergency medical attention is needed.
If I really suffer a heart attack, a stroke, or a sudden stop in breathing, then the window of time we have left to save my life is only four minutes—these are the “golden four minutes”!
It’s so important that the people around us know how to perform first aid!
When someone around us collapses, we can use our professional knowledge to help them. Instead of just standing there motionless and doing nothing, that feeling of helplessness is truly terrifying.
“In China, according to official data, three million people die accidentally each year. The most dangerous cause of death is sudden cardiac arrest.”
Across the United States, on average, 15% of people can be saved.
This is what Lu Le, the founder of First Reaction, said.
If a person experiences cardiac arrest, with no breathing or heartbeat, pressing the philtrum (the spot between the nose and the upper lip) will be of no use at all.
Artificial respiration and chest compressions must be performed in order to have a chance of saving the person.
I’ve noticed that not many people nowadays have the awareness to learn first aid skills. However, by the time something happens, it might already be too late. Therefore, I urge everyone to learn these skills so that we can respond promptly in case of emergencies.
Who knows? It might even save a person’s life!
You can sign up for a first aid certification at the local Red Cross training center. I registered at the Red Cross training center in Zhuhai, and there are even discounts available for students.
PS: The last picture shows the goals I set for myself to achieve before I turned 25. Adding a first-aid certification to that list was also something I did a few months ago, and I’ve actually accomplished it!
Next, I need to take exams for other certificates I want to obtain. I plan to get a scuba diving certificate. I saw on REDnote that there’s also a certification for first aid in diving, and it seems that you need to have a first aid certificate to be eligible to take the scuba diving exam. So, in fact, having a first aid certificate is really useful!
