Inspection of equipment for the production and processing of concrete modules for wells Introduction to Zhengzhou’s equipment for well wall brick modules:
Zhengzhou Yixin is a professional manufacturer of equipment for concrete inspection well modular brick production, as well as machinery for constructing inspection wells and well wall modules, offering production lines ranging from semi-automatic to fully automated.
Through years of practice and development, we have now established a reputation for producing high-quality equipment, primarily including hydraulic, mobile, and fully automated inspection well systems along with their accompanying accessories.
Inspection of the equipment used for the production and processing of concrete modules for inspection wells Zhengzhou: Assembly site for the equipment used for manufacturing well wall brick modules
Equipment for the production and processing of concrete modules for inspection wells Features and advantages of the equipment for well wall brick modules in Zhengzhou:
The Yixin check well block brick machine equipment is widely applicable to new types of masonry materials for municipal underground structures such as coal, heat, water, electricity, and gas facilities.
Examples include various inspection wells for drainage and water storage facilities, rainwater inlets, square ditches, septic tanks, small structures, and bridge wing walls.
The advantage of using concrete modules to construct inspection wells is that the modules have grooves on all their sides (upper, lower, left, and right), which when assembled together form a interlocking chain structure.
The shear resistance of the well wall is significantly better than that of the masonry constructed using plain friction bonding methods.
The module has a hollow structure; when assembled and laid together, the longitudinal holes are interconnected, and the transverse holes also intersect with each other. After the cores of these holes are poured with concrete, a cast-in-place concrete mesh structure is formed, which provides additional reinforcement and waterproofing benefits.
The module is equipped with reinforcement slots both horizontally and vertically; the horizontal reinforcement bars and vertical reinforcement rods correspondingly enhance the overall strength of the structure.
In addition, inspection wells and drainage wells constructed using concrete inspection well modules are less prone to collapse, subsidence, or leakage. The mechanical properties of the well wall modules are stable, the installation process is simple, and the formed dimensions meet standard requirements.
The intelligent control system for the concrete inspection well module brick manufacturing equipment is equipped with data input and output devices, as well as a one-touch touch-screen LCD display that monitors the entire mechanical operation process. This enables ideal human-machine interaction, automatic material ratio analysis, density control, safety logic management, and a fault diagnosis system.
The mechanical-hydraulic systems for the wellbore wall modules utilize single-cylinder and double-cylinder hydraulic technologies for both transportation and other functions.
The independent hydraulic integration station eliminates the impact of vibrations from the main machine on the hydraulic system, ensuring the reliability of its operation.
The equipment for manufacturing concrete inspection well modules includes a brick-making machine, a material distribution box, a traveling mold box, and a mold removal mechanism. The mold box rises after the process is completed, and the door of the material storage box closes automatically. The automatic conveying trays are also operated independently by the hydraulic system. This design aims to reduce mechanical wear and the need for maintenance.
The concrete inspection well module brick manufacturing equipment uses imported computers and electrical components, as well as seals and hydraulic parts, ensuring the overall stability and reliability of the equipment.
The mechanical vibration platform for the well wall module is constructed using integral sheet steel. The tabletop is precision-cut using wire cutting technology, and the joints are formed without any welding points, allowing the filler box to swing freely and guide its movement. This design significantly reduces mechanical wear and tear.
Reduce the mold load, combine the packing process with the vibration amplitude encryption function into one system; adopt an integrated and fully synchronized approach that includes both table vibration and mold vibration to ensure optimal compaction results.
The well wall module is mechanically excited using specialized equipment, with the amplitude automatically controlled by a computer based on the cost-effectiveness of the raw materials. This system eliminates wear and tear on braking components, thereby extending the module’s service life and reducing costs.
The well wall module features both mechanical automatic control and manual control functions.
Inspection of the well casing mold:
Yixin Brick Machine Inspection Well: The surface is constructed using cement blocks.
A corner of the workshop at Yixin Company:
Inspection of equipment for the production and processing of concrete modules for inspection wells
The Zhengzhou brick module equipment for well casing construction can not only produce inspection well blocks but also various types of standard bricks, hollow bricks, and decorative bricks for road surfaces.
