Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, May 20th (Huang Xiaoxi, Zhou Shanshan) Reporters learned from the China Children’s Center on the 20th that from May 28th to June 1st, around Children’s Day, the center plans to organize a series of events including children’s maker experiences, a children’s visual arts festival, and a parent-child book carnival, allowing children to celebrate Children’s Day in the charm of cutting-edge technology.
It is understood that the activities organized by the China Children’s Center during this year’s Children’s Day on June 1st include the “Love Home, Create Cool” Children’s Future Learning Carnival, the first Children’s Visual Arts Festival, the “Bookish Carnival,” and a series of activities related to picture books titled “The Whole Family Loves Reading.”
The event focuses on the organic integration of social innovation with the creative ideas of individuals and families. By involving children and families in various innovative educational activities, it aims to make innovative practices a cultural aspect of ordinary households, and to turn “doing things with hands” into a new way of learning and living for many families.
It is reported that the “Love Home, Create Cool” Children’s Future Learning Carnival includes various cutting-edge technology experiences, such as the “Douguo Maker” experience program, the anniversary celebration of the Lao Niu Children’s Exploration Museum and the “Explore Family Love, Have a Sweet Children’s Day” event, the VR public experience program, as well as the “Maker Tribe” interactive workshop, among dozens of other activities.
