Actually, there are many considerations when it comes to the clothing and styling for girls who are slightly overweight.
Girls who are overweight should not wear skirts that are too short or too long; the length should be around the knees, just enough to cover the areas of their thighs where they are thicker.
If a skirt is too short, it will highlight the fat on the legs.
If it’s too long, it can give the impression that someone is short and overweight.
If you wear clothes that are divided into three sections (top, middle, and bottom), it will make you appear taller naturally. Simply using different colors for the top, skirt, and stockings can create an effect that makes your figure look longer and more slender.
In fact, many dark-colored clothes are a staple for girls who are slightly overweight (the author can attest to this), as dark colors are an excellent way to conceal a fuller figure. Elegant and sophisticated black skirts are also a top choice for such girls.
Wearing dark-colored clothes, especially a black skirt, can make you appear slimmer.
If your calves are quite thick, avoid wearing socks and shoes that are too eye-catching.
The more popular it is, the better. The colors should also not be too bright.
To prevent people from noticing your legs and feet and thus giving the impression that you are overweight.
For slightly overweight girls, it’s really important to teach them the tricks of how to dress well and match their clothes properly.
Chubby girls should definitely avoid wearing tight, short skirts. Also, the tops should not be too short or tucked into the skirt, as this can look very uncomfortable. If your legs are thicker, wear black stockings or mesh stockings (the type with a fine pattern). Choose a soft, printed flared skirt and pair it with a top with a V-neck; this combination can effectively hide any perceived shortcomings.
Of course, even slightly plump girls have their own considerations when it comes to wearing short skirts.
A chubby girl wearing a short skirt should choose a top that matches the color of the skirt. This will create the illusion that her plump figure appears taller.
A short skirt paired with high heels can make your legs look longer and slimmer—this is definitely the most trendy combination for summer!
If you’re a girl with a fuller upper body but thinner legs, I recommend choosing a stylish one-piece skirt with a glamorous look.
It not only covers your big belly, but also highlights your best features.
A-line skirts can really make you look slimmer and are more suitable for girls who are a bit curvy. For the top, choose something that fits snugly; adding layers will also help create a slimming effect.
A simple white T-shirt paired with a short skirt – even plump girls can give it a try.
Even slightly plump girls can look stylish when they dress appropriately.
As long as they can master the rules of dressing and combining outfits, even slightly plump girls can become the center of attention for everyone.
Now that I’ve made changes to my clothing style, I also need to exercise more in my daily life and strive to get rid of the label of being a “slightly overweight girl” as soon as possible 😄
