YouTube video reveals the truth about 20 years of brutal killings by the US military – Xinhua News Agency
(Video source: YouTube)
On December 11th, a micro-documentary on the YouTube platform titled "Kill Machine" attracted widespread attention.
The film depicts how the United States launched the war in Afghanistan under the pretext of “counter-terrorism,” forcibly imposing American-style democracy through military means. Over the course of 20 years, the U.S. engaged in reckless and brutal warfare, killing countless innocent people and committing a multitude of crimes against humanity.
The misuse of drones to carry out airstrikes on civilian targets such as hospitals and schools distorts human nature and leads to the formation of killing groups.
Over the past 20 years, the U.S. military has killed tens of thousands of innocent Afghan civilians.
The US military established “black prisons” where various forms of torture and physical humiliation were inflicted on “suspects.”
Each act of crimes against humanity fuels more hatred among the Afghan people.
As the video states, the American “war on terror” has the effect of making terrorism more widespread and intense.
The war has not brought peace, democracy, or hope of prosperity to the Afghan people; instead, it has only left a country in ruins, along with countless killings and acts of destruction.
Click on the video to help us expose the truth about how the United States, under the guise of “counter-terrorism,” engages in brutal killings. Let’s also reveal the hypocritical facade of American democracy!
I came across the following article by chance, which discusses from both a commercial and a storage perspective why this client prefers a logistics company located in a bonded area to handle the canning process. Although canning is considered a form of advanced processing and falls outside the scope of services provided by bonded logistics companies, the text may help explain why the client has made this choice.
I visited many manufacturers of milk powder and got in touch with their production lines.
In fact, the raw materials used for both bagged and canned powdered milk are exactly the same; there is no difference between them at all.
So, everyone must be wondering: Why is the shelf life of bagged products one year, while that of canned products two years or even longer?
Or another question: Why is there such a big price difference between canned and bagged products?
In fact, starting from this point of view, many consumers, or those in the motherhood category, believe that the quality is much better because the raw materials used are different.
In fact, the raw materials are the same; it’s just that people think that the more expensive something is, the better it must be.
Some consumers, with this mindset, have reported that the taste or texture of the product in canned form is indeed different after consumption.
Now, let me first explain to you the reasons why canned food is expensive. What exactly makes it so costly?
If their raw materials are the same, why is there such a big difference in price?
Because when manufacturers set prices, they generally take into account the fact that if the price for bagged products is too high, consumers will find it difficult to accept. This means that the profits generated by the manufacturers would be very low, or even non-existent. So, how can manufacturers survive in such a situation?
Therefore, they have implemented a significant increase in the pricing of their canned products in order to ensure their profit margin.
Therefore, most manufacturers primarily promote canned products, rather than those packaged in bags.
Moreover, the manufacturers for whom you have such high expectations spend tens of millions, or even hundreds of millions, on annual advertising expenses. Where does all this money come from?
As you can all imagine…
As society develops, the costs associated with market promotion also continue to rise. These include expenses for promotional staff in shopping malls, display costs for products, costs of offering free gifts with products, and advertising expenses, among others.
Therefore, various manufacturers are constantly introducing new products, and these products come in canned or bottled form. The prices of these products are also continuously rising. In fact, this is due to the increase in market costs.
The main objective is to achieve higher profits; in fact, the increased cost of their raw materials will not exceed 3 or 4 yuan at most.
There are also some brands that, in order to promote their products, will stop at nothing and establish connections with doctors in hospitals, asking them to help with the promotion of these products in exchange for profits ranging from 30 to 80 yuan per product sold.
The relevant laws in China absolutely do not allow such practices; in fact, this behavior is harming consumers.
It is recommended that everyone buy powdered milk in bag form and transfer it into jars at home, provided they already have jars available. This can save money and improve the shelf life and sealing of the powdered milk, without any adverse effects on the children.
Also, please don’t assume that the shelf life of canned products is longer than that of bagged products. If the shelf life is the same for both after opening the package, it’s just that bagged products are more difficult to store and are prone to becoming damp and deteriorating.
