Is it because of an electric leak that my feet go numb when soaking them in a foot bath tub?
Choosing the right foot bath tub can have a significant positive effect on foot care and health. Today, the editor from Gome will provide answers to this question, hoping it will be helpful to our friends.
As people's awareness of health and wellness increases, foot bath tubs have become increasingly popular among consumers. A wide range of products with different prices is available on the market, ranging from just over a hundred yuan to several thousand yuan, providing consumers with a great deal of choice.
According to the available data, health-related home appliances such as foot baths are selling very well compared to traditional household appliances. However, there are no specific industry standards for foot baths, which poses certain safety risks.
Mr. Li told the reporters that recently he bought a foot bath for his father as a birthday gift. However, when his father used the foot bath, he felt numbness in the soles of his feet.
At first, Mr. Li thought it was the vibration function of the foot bath tub causing the problem. To his surprise, even after turning off the vibration function, his father still felt a tingling sensation in the soles of his feet.
Mr. Li used a test pen to check, and to his surprise, the pen lit up. He then discovered that the water in the foot bath was actually electrically charged.
Later, he contacted the merchant, and the merchant’s attitude was quite good. Although the foot bath tub was returned, Mr. Li still felt dissatisfied.
Because he found that there are no clear and detailed industry regulations regarding the currently popular foot bath tubs – in terms of the highest temperature settings, the target user groups, or the materials used to ensure safety.
However, in general, foot bath tubs should not have any electrical safety issues. Nevertheless, it is possible that a small number of products may not have undergone strict quality control before leaving the factory.
Therefore, when making a purchase, choose a split-type foot bath tub.
The separation of water and electricity poses no safety hazards at all.
At the same time, you can use a stylus to measure whatever you want.
