A beginner in programming who wants to share their personal experiences.
If you plan to enter this industry, you could consider finding a place for training. However, if you don’t have such intentions, it’s best to learn on your own. After all, training can be quite expensive, and it will also take you six months to complete.
But if you plan to enter this industry, training is indeed a very good option, especially for those with weak self-control. Training is even more beneficial in such cases.
If you have a strong sense of self-control, you can also choose to study on your own, but it will probably be more exhausting.
Of course, choosing a good training institution is a very important matter.
First and foremost, it is important to look at the teaching staff of the institution. If the teaching staff is not strong enough, then the training program has little value. Of course, some newly established training institutions may not have a particularly strong teaching staff.
Secondly, before making a choice, it’s advisable to do some research on the training institution. It would be best to talk to some of the students who have graduated from this institution, as only they can truly provide insights into how the institution is and whether the courses offered are of good quality or not.
Hello, actually, I don’t know how to answer your question either, because you haven’t provided any information about your own situation. Learning something is closely related to an individual’s personal circumstances.
For example, your major, age, the language you want to learn, and even the city you live in – all these factors are related to the industry you plan to study or work in.
If you are a student and have not yet graduated, or if you are a computer science graduate, then I personally recommend self-study if you have enough time. This is the most efficient and cost-effective option. There are many excellent training institutions both offline and online nowadays, but the learning cost is high, and it requires a significant amount of time; typically, you need to attend intensive training for 3 to 6 months.
But if it’s the situations I mentioned, self-study would be very convenient. There are many learning resources available online for free, and there are also plenty of training materials on Bilibili. If you don’t know how to find these resources, you can contact me through the introduction provided; I can help you obtain free materials or offer detailed guidance.
There are also some more classic books that can be used in combination with videos for a comprehensive learning experience.
If you are not majoring in computer science but are willing to invest the necessary money and time in learning, it is recommended that you enroll in a training institution. This approach makes the learning process less challenging, as the instructors provide detailed explanations, and there are people available to answer any questions you may have. Additionally, training institutions can offer assistance with planning your studies and providing supervision.
Moreover, many training institutions nowadays sign employment agreements and offer internal referral opportunities. After completing the training, students are recommended for jobs at relevant companies, which can save a lot of time during the subsequent job interview process.
The above are some of my thoughts. As I didn’t know much about your situation, the explanation I gave was only general and not detailed. If you have any other questions or concerns, you can contact me at any time to discuss them further.
