Second, although the right has had its moments of success in history, these periods have not been long-lasting. The reason for this is that they become overly enthusiastic with even the slightest amount of attention or encouragement; they quickly become overambitious when they achieve a little success, but lose all direction and coherence when faced with setbacks.
But to be realistic, the right has played a positive role in the process of social progress.
In terms of ending the Cultural Revolution, establishing standards for determining truth, developing the economy, advancing science and technology, as well as promoting the institutionalization of administrative systems and the protection of human rights, the positive contributions of the right-wing should not be denied.
Thirdly, as for me, although I do not completely agree with some of Li Weidong’s statements, I take his views seriously and respect him as a person. He is sincere; he is serious about China and also takes a serious attitude towards China’s social issues.
However, I oppose his anti-communist theories. I believe that counter-revolutionary efforts are unnecessary; revolutions inevitably lead to social unrest, harm to people’s livelihoods, and a situation where political groups become mixed and degraded in quality. Moreover, foreign countries may take advantage of such vulnerabilities.
Fourth, any efforts to change or improve China require patience and a sense of responsibility towards the country and its people. Those who engage in political opportunism, trying to gain advantage from difficult situations, are not right-wing; they are simply scoundrels.
Let’s talk about the left again.
On the left, there are actually a group of people who have been abandoned by their times and by politics.
If it can be said that the right holds positive significance for society, and the Communist Party is still willing to listen to certain views from the right and analyze their ideas when necessary, then the left does not have such fortune. After all, what the left seeks are precisely the very flaws and bad aspects that the Communist Party aims to eliminate!
