From the past to the present, I have always opposed any form of slander and abuse, and I certainly cannot tolerate such personal attacks.
In civilized societies, we should be able to tolerate everything, but we must put an end to such villains.
If we set aside political parties and factions, the first thing we need to resist is this uncivilized behavior.
Since you started by sending requests to add me as a friend on Facebook, then posted sarcastic messages, and later tried to share the location of what you call my home and my father’s name on social media, I have chosen to remain unresponsive.
Later on, you not only continued to tag me at an even more frequent rate (six times a day), but also went on to discuss me in rather explicit and humiliating ways on Facebook with your so-called friends. Comments about my appearance, body, fertility, and even things like “planting strawberries in bed” or whether I should use certain devices during intercourse… Well, I’ll just let it go.
Later on, I received messages from several friends regarding a photo of you that had been uploaded to your Facebook profile, along with comments that contained elements of sexual harassment.
I’m sorry, but as a girl, I can no longer remain silent any longer.
After the news about my report to the police was uploaded, you didn’t show any sign of changing your behavior at all; instead, you became even more arrogant.
I don’t care what your political background is, or what your social status is; in our society, it is necessary for both genders to be respected.
Yes, you can continue with these sarcastic, subtle, humiliating, and abusive remarks. You can also keep saying that you just have good intentions and are concerned about me. You can continue to think that this isn’t harassment, and you might even deny that the images were made by you or continue to make any other offensive statements.
That’s right; I can’t, and I don’t have the ability to stop you.
I don’t know you, and I don’t want to know you. Moreover, your opinions about my appearance and figure are completely irrelevant to me.
I don’t even think there would be a single girl who would agree to let someone humiliate her in such a way just in exchange for fame.
A friend asked me if I was okay.
Even if I say yes, you wouldn’t believe me.
I don’t think there would be a single girl who, after being bullied in such a way, could still say that she’s okay.
Whether in the workplace, society, politics, or business, only those who lack even basic moral principles would choose to harm any woman in such a manner.
I believe that fairness lies within people’s hearts.
I’ve selected some of the comments for everyone to review and discuss.
